Description:
Airbnb tries to solve problems like price concerns when booking travel online and 
    difficulties in booking rooms with locals. Our solution si a web platform where users can rent out their space
    to host travellers.Functionalities: search by city, review listings, book it. Competitive advantage: first to market, 
    ease of use, profiles, list once, design and brand, host incentive. Business model: we take 10% commission on each transaction
Testimonials:
A complete success! It is easy to use and made me money!- Emily M, Austin TX, 

    AirBed & Breakfast freaking rocks! -Jouse F, Washington DC, 

     It's about the ideas, the interactions, the people. You don't get that in a hotel room - Dan A, Ontario, Canada
Story:
Shortly after moving to San Francisco in October 2007, we came up with the idea of putting an 
    air mattress in our living room and 
    turning it into a bed and breakfast.[6] In February 2008, Nathan Blecharczyk, a former roommate,
     joined as the Chief Technology Officer and the third co-founder of the new venture, which we named 
     AirBed & Breakfast. We put together a website that offered short-term living quarters, 
     breakfast, and a business networking opportunity for those who were unable to book a hotel in the 
     saturated market.[6] The site Airbedandbreakfast.com officially launched on August 11, 2008. 
     We had our first customers in town in the summer of 2008, during the Industrial Design Conference held by 
     Industrial Designers Society of America, where travelers had a hard time finding lodging in the city
USP: Book rooms with locals rather than hotels

Description:
The problem that we are trying to solve is that taxi-monopolies reduce quality of service.
    Our solution is to create a fast and efficient on-demand car service which offers the conveniece of a cab
    plus the experience of a professional chuffeur. Our key differentiators: optimized fleet, fast response time, 
    luxury automobiles, high-tech solutions. Uber uses a dynamic pricing model; 
    prices for the same route vary according to supply and demand for rides at the time that the ride is requested
Testimonials:
I was hesitant at first because I'm a woman. 
    
    I just wanted to make enough money every week to help pay some bills. 
    
    I decided to get the course and now I'm making an average of $645 a week. I couldn't be happier. - Samira 
    Smith, student
Story:
We founded Uber in 2009 as UberCab by
    On New Year's Eve, after me and my friends spent $800 hiring a private driver, I wanted to find a
    way to reduce the cost of direct transportation. I realized that sharing the cost with people could 
    make it affordable, and my idea morphed into Uber. Kalanick  later joined me.The first prototype was 
    built by me and my friends, Oscar Salazar and Conrad Whelan,
    with Kalanick being brought on as a mega advisor to the company.

Description:
Sidebean tries to solve the problem of the great amount of time it takes to build a professional slide 
    presentation, plus the fact that power point alternative tools are eqully inefficient, with long learning curves.
    Our solution consists in a unique ui algorithm that automatically redesigns user content and automatic 
    engagement tracking for each slide, ideal for sales pitch decks. 
    Our competitive technology advantages are: fully indexable slide content, html5 render on the Client Side
    and Flickr, Giphy and NounProject Integrations.
Testimonials:
Wow... Blown away by the massive value your team keeps bringing to the table...
    William Martin, Podcast Academy 
, Awesome work! Thank you your help, my slides look great now.
    Shelby Davies, Firstbrook Insurance Group 
, Thanks for all your hard work. We appreciate your attention, politeness and speed in handling our request.
    Stephen Ryan, Wow Now Go!
Story:
We started Slidebean because we believe that great design can be applied to almost all aspects 
    of life: from 
    how people share and absorb information to everyday interactions with our environment, and experiences 
    with other people. 
    Every month, we invest 1% of our subscription revenue on initiatives that use design to change the world!
USP: Design automation is our ultimate goal

Description:
Fittr is a workout generator that takes in user equipment  access, time commitment, and 
    goals for working out. After taking in this info, Fittr uses a GPU supercomputing cluster to create a great
    individualized workoout plan.Fittr not only creates great workouts, it learns from users data and then makes
    better workout. Fittr has a unique accountability tool that tells users' friends when they skip a 
    workout as well as group features and trophies to keep you motivated
Testimonials:
This is everything that i ever wanted in an app that would help me towards my fitness 
    journey, infact it has few things that i dint imagine!! And this not an exaggeration this is a fact! 
    Thanks Fittr team! - Varsha Gujar 
, Awesome experience, it's a wonderful app to get fitter, 
    using quantified nutrition and strength training lost 14 kgs building strength happy with Fittr -Kelly, San
    Francisco
Story:
Hey, my name is Jitendra Chouksey. FITTR (formerly known as SQUATS) started as a WhatsApp group 
    where I would help my friends and family members get fit. When some of them got results, they told others
    and soon I was being chased by a lot of people who wanted me to make them fit. It wasn’t easy for me to 
    help so many people and so I started educating them. 
    After all, getting fit isn’t exactly rocket science!
USP: A Fitter, Better and a Smarter World!

Description:
dribble is a premium marketplace of the best designer talent where the talent picks the
    work. How does it work? Well, there are a few steps: 
 1. Pitch your idea. 2. Chooose favourte implementation
    styles 3. The single best pro comes to you. 
 Our vision is to become the most trusteed, collabortive 
    marketplace in the world.
Testimonials:
dribbble changed the way I work and with that how i live - Steve, photoshop illustrator, 

    Dribbble has really impacted my career in a big way. Especially when I was trying to break into the 
    tech industry - Hannah - desinger and illustrator
Story:
Founded in 2009, we are a bootstrapped and profitable company helping design talent share,
     grow, and get hired by over 40,000 of today’s most innovative brands around the world. Tens of millions
     of people look for design inspiration and feedback on Dribbble. We help players like you share small screenshots (shots) to show off your current projects, 
     boost your portfolio, and love what you do—no matter what kind of creative professional you are.

Description:
Founders Fund is an venture capital fund. As co-investors, we invest in 
      high-growth start-ups in their later seed and early stage phase. As a long-term partner, we offer both 
      start-up and follow-up financing.
      The objective of aws Founders Fund is to establish a partnership among equals with 
      portfolio companies and to offer a supportive role in establishing a market position as well as 
      achieving and maintaining sustainable growth.
Testimonials:
I found people that not only believed in my idea, but were willing to act like
      true partners, offering valuable advice. Mikael- Neoh .
  With the help of Founders Fund I have 
      accomplished things I wouldn't otherwise dreamt of, they are truly a team of professionsals.
Story:
Formed in 2005, Founders Fund had more than $3 billion in aggregate capital under management
       as of 2016. The firm invests across all stages and sectors, including aerospace, artificial 
       intelligence, advanced computing, energy, health, and consumer Internet, with a portfolio that 
       includes Airbnb, Lyft, Spotify, Stripe, and Oscar Health. Founders Fund was the first institutional 
       investor in Space Exploration Technologies (SpaceX) and Palantir Technologies, and one of the
       earliest investors in Facebook. The firm’s partners, including Peter Thiel, Ken Howery and
       Brian Singerman, have been founders, early employees and investors at companies including PayPal,
       Google, Palantir Technologies, and SpaceX.

Description:
Hummingbird Ventures is an agile investor in
      entrepreneurial genius.
      
      We value emotional intelligence as much as data,
      growing internal culture as much as growing revenue,
      and forming strong, personal bonds with founders.
      
      Often the ﬁrst institutional investor, we’ve helped
      start-ups scale from zero to category-defining
      multi-billion dollar businesses across 3 continents
      
      We work best with outsiders who challenge industry
      boundaries and conventions, transforming tiny
      miracles into impactful companies.
